1489.description:
Feature: 
Scenario Outline: User is a valid Amazon.com user that is currently logged out, but wants to access their account.
 Given that I'm a logged-out Amazon.com user on the sign-in page
 When I fill in the "Username" and "Password" fields with my authentication credentials
 and I click the Sign-In button
 Then the system signs me in
1489.name: Signing In to Amazon.com using a valid username and password

1531.description:
As a logged-out Amazon.com user

I want to be able to sign in to Amazon.com

So that I can access my Amazon account
1531.name: Logging into Amazon.com

2219.description: User enters a valid Username into the “Username” field
2219.expectedResult: Username is successfully entered into the Username field
2219.sampleData: Username is for a currently enrolled user, and contains only alpha and numeric characters

2220.description: User enters a valid Password into the “Password” field
2220.expectedResult: Password is successfully entered into the Password field
2220.sampleData: Password entered contains only alpha and numeric characters, and is more than 8, but less than 16 characters
